---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About" description="Why we build HelixGitpx.">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-5xl font-semibold">About HelixGitpx</h1>
    <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-slate-700">
      HelixGitpx was born from a single question: when your Git host goes
      down for eight hours, what is your team supposed to do?
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-slate-700">
      For most teams, the answer is "wait". That's an unacceptable answer
      for the software industry in 2026. We think source control is too
      important to depend on a single vendor — and that federation is the
      only mental model that actually solves the problem.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 text-2xl font-semibold">Principles</h2>
    <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-slate-700 list-disc list-inside">
      <li><strong>Open source.</strong> Apache-2.0 for code, CC-BY-SA-4.0 for docs. Self-host or hosted — your choice.</li>
      <li><strong>Federation over migration.</strong> We don't ask you to leave your existing hosts. We ask you to add more.</li>
      <li><strong>Policy as code.</strong> Every enforcement is in a signed bundle. No magic.</li>
      <li><strong>AI with guardrails.</strong> Useful AI, honest about hallucinations, kill-switchable per org.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="mt-12 text-2xl font-semibold">Team</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-slate-700">
      Founded 2025 by <strong>Милош Васић</strong>. See
      <a href="/careers" class="text-primary hover:underline">/careers</a>
      for open roles.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 text-2xl font-semibold">Where we're based</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-slate-700">
      Distributed. Legal entity in Berlin. Engineers across Serbia, Russia,
      Germany, and the UK.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
